Step 1: Verify Current Setup
  ├─ Confirm OctoPrint is running on Pi
  ├─ Confirm printer is connected to Pi
  └─ Confirm webcam is working

Step 2: Document Your Setup
  ├─ Create a README with hardware/software versions
  ├─ Document network configuration
  └─ Record any custom settings or plugins

Step 3: Access OctoPrint Remotely
  ├─ Verify local access (same network)
  ├─ Set up OctoPrint API key for programmatic access
  └─ Consider security (authentication, HTTPS)

Step 4: Build Your Autonomous Features
  ├─ Create scripts to monitor printer state
  ├─ Add visual feedback processing (webcam)
  └─ Implement automation logic

Step 5: Version Control & Documentation
  ├─ Initialize Git repository
  ├─ Document your code and setup
  └─ Track your progress
